# 👥 User Management System - C++ OOP

![C++](https://img.shields.io/badge/C%2B%2B-00599C?style=for-the-badge&logo=c%2B%2B&logoColor=white)
![Status](https://img.shields.io/badge/status-learning-blue?style=for-the-badge)

---

## 📌 About the Project

This is a simple C++ object-oriented program that models a basic user system with inheritance.

It includes two types of users:
- Operario (Worker)
- Manager

---

## 🚀 Features

- 🧱 Inheritance (`Usuario` base class)
- 👷 Operario class
- 👨‍💼 Manager class
- 📧 User information handling
- 🖥️ Console output

---

## 🛠️ Technologies

- C++
- Standard Library (`iostream`, `string`)

---

## 💻 How it works

1. Create user objects
2. Assign data (name, email, role/department)
3. Display formatted output

---

## 🎯 Learning Goals

- Understand inheritance in C++
- Practice class structure
- Learn encapsulation
- Improve OOP design thinking

---

## 🔮 Future Improvements

- Add constructors
- Add polymorphism
- Store users in a list (vector)
- Add menu system for input

